rooms.name: center
rooms.description: cold and dimly lit. The wind is whistling under the door.

sites.name: Botany
sites.file_content: It is an image file with hundreds of microscope images of plant cells.

sites.name: Engineering
sites.file_content: Note to self: it would be SO easy to murder someone on this station lol

items.name: newspaper
items.description: The yellowing paper is barely readable. The headline is about last year's election.

items.name: knife
items.description: Worn, but still sharp enough to hurt.

items.name: note
items.description: It reads 'To do: change the admin login away from the default.'

items.name: paperweight
items.description: A pyramid of smoked quartz the size of a fist.

items.name: diary
items.description: It's written in a language you don't recognise - perhaps some sort of cipher.

help_tips.clear: Clears the terminal of all previous interactions.
help_tips.drop: Syntax: drop [object]. Moves an object from your inventory to the inventory of the current room.
help_tips.inspect: Syntax: inspect [room|object]. Can be used to get more information about your current room, or a description of an object in your inventory or in the current room.
help_tips.login: Syntax: login [username] [password]. Different logins have different permissions, and potentially accesss to different information.
help_tips.move: Syntax: move [room]. Use to move to an adjacent room with an unlocked door. Requires energy; the more items in your inventory, the more energy it takes.
help_tips.recharge: Syntax: recharge [amount]. Recharges power by that amount or to 100%, whichever is lower. Must be a whole number.
help_tips.take: Syntax: take [object]. Moves an object from the current room to your inventory.
help_tips.unlock: Syntax: unlock [room] [password]. Unlocks a locked door accessible from your current room.

Please log in using your M-NET credentials to continue.
